[03:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'faster than Hunen? So, here\'s the method. It first learns from a pre-trained or an existing video model. And this model takes multiple steps to generate a video. So, for all diffusion'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'models out there, which include image and video generators, they basically start with a frame of latent noise that looks like this. And then for each step, it takes away some of that noise until eventually you get your final image or'

[04:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video frame. So for most of these leading video generators, they do take multiple steps to take away enough noise so you actually get a clear video. Well, this new model basically looks at all'

[04:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the steps from this existing model. And so it can see the first step of the generation process and the final step of the generation process. And then it just learns to skip all these middle steps and learns to generate the video from'

[04:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the first step to the final step. So this is called trajectory based few step guidance where they trained this new model to basically skip all the steps in the middle and then they also use a special technique called adversarial'

[04:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'training strategy. And this is used to further improve the quality of the generated videos by matching it to the style of this pre-trained or existing video model. Anyways, if you scroll up to the top of the page, the good news is'

